Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as named entity recognition (NER) from speech. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech data and automatic speech recognition (ASR) systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper uses a neural architecture for end-to-end named entity extraction. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses a joint optimization approach for both ASR and NER, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.SD (Signal Processing) is another possible category as the paper deals with processing audio signals for ASR and NER tasks.
